      "rationale": "Code verification performed against three analytical benchmark problems: (1) Hagen-Poiseuille flow in a straight tube (L2 error < 0.02% on finest mesh), (2) Taylor-Couette flow between rotating cylinders (velocity profile error < 0.1%), and (3) lid-driven cavity at Re=1000 (streamfunction extrema within 0.3% of Ghia et al. reference). Manufactured solution verification (MMS) confirms second-order spatial accuracy for momentum and scalar transport equations. All verification cases archived and independently reproduced.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
