      "rationale": "Systematic mesh refinement study conducted on three geometrically similar meshes (coarse: 2.1M cells, medium: 6.8M cells, fine: 18.4M cells). Grid convergence index (GCI) computed per Roache (1994) for NIH, pump head, and torque. Fine-mesh GCI for NIH: 2.3% (95% CI); for pump head: 1.8%. Observed convergence order p=1.94 (theoretical 2.0). Production simulations use fine mesh. Temporal discretization verified via time-step refinement (Δt = 1e-4 s production; 5e-5 s refinement — NIH change < 0.8%).",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/discretization-error",
