    "rationale": "The UnitOfAssurance for COU2 at MRL 5 is accepted based on the following structured evidence summary. All 13 credibility factors have been assessed at the required level (5) and all achieved levels meet or exceed requirements (achieved level 5 for all factors). The quantitative validation evidence demonstrates model adequacy: NIH prediction error is within the combined validation uncertainty (ASME V&V 20 metric satisfied), pump head error is 4.2% against a 7% threshold, and velocity field RMS error is 7.8% against a 10% threshold. Uncertainty quantification via Sobol quasi-Monte Carlo (N=500) and polynomial chaos expansion establishes 95% confidence intervals on all primary QoIs, confirming that the relative hemolysis index RH < 1 acceptance criterion is met with high confidence across the full operating envelope. The global sensitivity analysis identifies rotational speed and inlet flow rate as dominant uncertainty contributors (Sobol S1 = 0.41 and 0.33 respectively), and these parameters have been measured with calibrated instruments (±5 RPM, ±0.5% flow) ensuring tight control of the dominant uncertainty sources. Software QA, code verification, and use error controls are fully implemented at MRL 5 rigor with independent review and cross-solver verification. The model form assessment demonstrates robustness to turbulence model choice (NIH variation < 9%) and validates the Newtonian rheology assumption (< 4% NIH difference versus non-Newtonian). The validation activities are directly relevant to the COU across all 8 similarity dimensions. The provenance chain is complete from foundational experimental data through validation results to this credibility assessment. No weakeners were identified. The assessment team concludes that the CFD hemolysis model provides sufficient credibility to support the regulatory decision for the Class II CPB device under the stated operating envelope.",
